- Purpose:
  - Provides file "slurping".
  - To slurp a file is to read it, in its entirety, into core.
- Comments
  - slurp ( caddr u -- )
    - Reads the file specified by (caddr u) into RAM at HERE.
    - ALLOTs as necessary
    - Caller is assumed to keep track of HERE to determine final buffer size
    - Caller is assumed to understand that enough dictionary space exists to hold the file read.

